description:
The second season of Jujutsu Kaisen.

The past comes to light when second-year students Satoru Gojou and Suguru Getou are tasked with escorting young Riko Amanai to Master Tengen. But when a non-sorcerer user tries to kill them, their mission to protect the Star Plasma Vessel threatens to turn them into bitter enemies and cement their destinies—one as the world’s strongest sorcerer, and the other its most twisted curse user!

(Source: Crunchyroll)

__Introduction:__
Tatsuya Kitani is a Japanese vocalist, bassist, guitarist, composer, arranger and programmer. He is also known as a Vocaloid song producer, going under the name Konnichiwa Tanita-san/Hello Tanita-san.

__Biography:__
Tatsuya started publishing music on the Internet around 2014. Later in 2017, he would start performing solo activities, while providing music as a lyricist. In 2018, he would form the band [Sajou no Hana](https://anilist.co/staff/137163) (stylized as sajou no hana) with members Sana and [Sho Watanabe](https://anilist.co/staff/109345).

__[Website](https://sakiyamasoushi.com/) | [Twitter](https://twitter.com/soushiclub) | [Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/soush.i_sakiyama/) | [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCBrgK9ZtiUn0Gmn3cruQBkA) | [TikTok](https://www.tiktok.com/@sakiyamasoushi_official?)__

__Birthplace:__ Hamamatsu City, Shizuoka Prefecture, Japan

__Soushi Sakiyama__ is a Japanese vocalist, lyricist and composer under record labels Sony Music Label (2020–) and Sony Music Records (2021–), he is also affiliated with the entertainment office Sony Music Entertainment. He has been active as a musician since 2015, where he began focusing on street performances and live events. 

He made his major label debut 6 years later on January 27, 2021, with the album "find fuse in youth". Between his major label debut and his debut as a musician, he also wrote and performed a theme song titled "Awa Mitaku Kagayaite" in the 2019 drama _Heisei Monogatari_ in the second season "Nan Demokaideredo, Kakegae no Nai Shunkan", while also debuting in anime with his ending theme "Undulation" in the show _2.43: Seiin High School Boys Volleyball Team_.
__Keiji Oota__ is a Japanese producer and animation planner. Managing Director at Toho.
__Yoshihisa Heishi__ is a Japanese magazine editor, animation planner and producer. He currently works for Shueisha and was an editor-in-chief for Weekly Shounen Jump between 2011-2017.

Began his career in animation at [Studio 4°C](https://anilist.co/studio/13/), where he worked on projects like [Genius Party Beyond](https://anilist.co/anime/6795/). In 2011, he was handpicked by then president [Masao Maruyama](https://anilist.co/staff/103170/) to join [Mappa](https://anilist.co/studio/569/) as a producer. He then went on to work as an animation producer on numerous titles such as [Kids on the Slope](https://anilist.co/anime/12531/), [Terror in Resonance](https://anilist.co/anime/20661/) and [Shingeki no Bahamut: Genesis](https://anilist.co/anime/20590/).

In April 2016, Maruyama handed Ootsuka the reigns of the studio and he took on the role of a producer and the CEO.

Hiroo Maruyama is a producer working for Mainichi Broadcasting System (MBS).

He joined Mainichi Broadcasting in 1999. Was transferred later to the Tokyo office and took over duties relating to the production of animation broadcasts. He was responsible for production on series like Gundam Seed, Gundam Seed Destiny and Full Metal Alchemist, all part of the 6:00pm Saturday timeblock, which gained wide popularity.
